	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />N64 on a 600 P3 is impressive, I would have guessed it would need lots more.  Wonder how much of that is off loaded onto the graphics card.
<br />
<br />You should be able to easily get fresh XP install down to 30 secs boot time.  There are tons of services you can turn off.  Finding a system that sleeps and wakes correctly would be faster, laptop should do that fine.  Adding the composite output to a laptop is harder tho.  The main issues with just used desktop PCs would be the size and noise.  If its hidden or inside a cabinet that may not matter.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


